Freddie LLM backend integration: (1) acptoapi bridge — integrated at src/agent/acptoapi-bridge.js + src/agent/llm_resolver.js (commit 5f55f1e). Localhost API (default port 4800) converting OpenAI/Anthropic SDK calls to multiple backends: Kilo Code, opencode, Claude CLI, Anthropic API, Gemini, Ollama, Bedrock. Endpoint /v1/chat/completions, OpenAI-compatible, accepts Bearer none auth. (2) acptoapi dep pattern (2026-05-12) — package.json pins "acptoapi": "^1.0.55" from npm registry (CI auto-bumps; restore-package.cjs ROOT FIX prevents file: regressions). For local SDK iteration, swap to file:../acptoapi. CJS/ESM boundary bridged via createRequire(import.meta.url) in freddie ESM files importing acptoapi CJS exports. (3) LLM resolver priority (2026-05-10): (a) explicit provider+key, (b) acptoapi if /v1/models returns 200, (c) agent.model_preference config array (ordered failover, sampler-gated), (d) sdk.buildAutoChain() env-key scan, (e) throw. PROVIDER_KEYS and PROVIDER_DEFAULTS imported from acptoapi. sdk.chat() returns OpenAI format; sdkChat() adapter converts to freddie's {content, tool_calls, raw}. (4) Model sampler — direct acptoapi import (2026-05-17): src/agent/model-sampler.js deleted. Sampler funcs come straight from acptoapi via createRequire. Backoff logic (5-step 30s→480s) lives in c:\dev\acptoapi\lib\sampler.js. (5) model_preference config key — agent.model_preference: [] in ~/.freddie/config.yaml. Array of {provider, model?}; resolveCallLLM tries each in order, sampler-gated. Config v2 migration adds key on upgrade from v1.